<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0212-sn">

   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Letter Signed: a letter not in the authors handwriting, but signed by the author ]">LS</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>;

<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Draft: a draft of a letter or document in the handwriting of someone other than the author ]">Df</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Massachusetts Historical Society, Boston ]">MHi</span> Sayer-Gilman Papers;

copy, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Maine Historical Society, Portland ]">MeHi</span>.

The two committees sent a similar letter to the Massachusetts General Court on this date. See <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Collections of the Maine Historical Society&lt;/i&gt;. Portland, Maine, 18311916. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Maine Hist. Soc. Col.</span></span>, 2d ser., 14 (1910), 31618.</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0212-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0212-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>For accounts of the burning of Falmouth on 18 Oct., see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-02-02-0179" class="document">Portsmouth Committee of Safety to GW, 19 Oct.</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-02-02-0181" class="document">Reuben Fogg to GW, 20 Oct.</a>, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-02-02-0210-0002" class="document">Deposition of Pearson Jones, this date</a>, enclosed in <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-02-02-0210-0001" class="document">GW to Hancock, this date</a>.</p>

